Uses of Interface
net.jini.core.entry.Entry

  • Packages that use Entry 
    Package Description
    net.jini.core.entry
    The Entry interface and its associated UnusableEntryException are used by the lookup service to represent service-specific attributes and by the JavaSpace interface to mark entries.
    net.jini.core.lookup
    These are the lookup service interfaces and classes.

      Entry CloneableEntry.clone()
      Clone has been implemented in AbstractEntry to allow utilities such as net.jini.lookup.ServiceDiscoveryManager to avoid sharing internally stored mutable Entry instances with client code.
